<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1016,1223]" box="[151,726,1052,1080]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1052,1079]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Distribution:</emphasis>
Southern Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Pauly, A. &amp; Pesenko, Y. &amp; Radchenko, V." box="[517,714,1053,1080]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref22368" refString="Pauly, A., Pesenko, Y. &amp; Radchenko, V. (2016) Les Halictus Latreille, 1804 d'Europe et du Bassin Mediterraneen. Atlas Hymenoptera, Mons, Belgium. Available from: http: // www. atlashymenoptera. net / page. asp? id = 70 (accessed 12 March 2020)" type="url" year="2016">
Pauly 
<emphasis box="[590,639,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1016,1223]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,1089,1115]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Notes:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klug in Germar" authorityYear="1817" box="[234,460,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetrazonius">
<emphasis box="[234,460,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Halictus tetrazonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is another 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[583,678,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[583,678,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Halictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species that cannot be confidently identified in the female sex. This species has been misidentified in the past, and is probably absent from 
<collectingCountry box="[1014,1090,1125,1151]" name="France" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pauly, A. &amp; Pesenko, Y. &amp; Radchenko, V." box="[1107,1306,1125,1152]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref22368" refString="Pauly, A., Pesenko, Y. &amp; Radchenko, V. (2016) Les Halictus Latreille, 1804 d'Europe et du Bassin Mediterraneen. Atlas Hymenoptera, Mons, Belgium. Available from: http: // www. atlashymenoptera. net / page. asp? id = 70 (accessed 12 March 2020)" type="url" year="2016">
Pauly 
<emphasis box="[1181,1232,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1371,1436,1125,1151]" name="Georgia" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Iberia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J. &amp; Pauly, A." box="[205,539,1161,1187]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref21974" refString="Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J. &amp; Pauly, A. (2017) Contribution a la connaissance des Halictinae d'Espagne, avec un atlas des especes de la Peninsule Iberique (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae). Belgian Journal of Entomology, 54, 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="2017">Ortiz-Sánchez &amp; Pauly 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Because the only records from 
<collectingCountry box="[913,1008,1161,1187]" name="Portugal" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Portugal</collectingCountry>
were made from female material, the species is removed from the Portuguese list.
</paragraph>
