<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1268,1547]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,1413,1439]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Notes:</emphasis>
Currently only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Morawitz" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[407,579,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibulare">
<emphasis box="[407,579,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">L. mandibulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[780,875,1413,1439]" name="Portugal" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baldock, D. &amp; Wood, T. J. &amp; Cross, I. &amp; Smit, J." box="[889,1117,1413,1439]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref20369" refString="Baldock, D., Wood, T. J., Cross, I. &amp; Smit, J. (2018) The Bees of Portugal. Entomofauna, Supplement 22, 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="2018">
Baldock 
<emphasis box="[992,1042,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perez" baseAuthorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aglyphum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">L. aglyphum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unclear, and it may be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Morawitz" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[775,947,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibulare">
<emphasis box="[775,947,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">L. mandibulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is found in North Africa, Sicily, 
<collectingCountry box="[1367,1432,1449,1475]" name="Israel" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Israel</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[244,289,1485,1511]" name="Iran" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pauly, A." box="[303,449,1485,1512]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref22232" refString="Pauly, A. (2016 b) Les Dialictus Robertson, 1902 de la Region Palearctique. Atlas Hymenoptera, Mons, Belgium. Available from: http: // www. atlashymenoptera. net / page. asp? id = 128 (accessed 12 March 2020)" type="url" year="2016">Pauly 2016b</bibRefCitation>
). For now, material from 
<collectingCountry box="[730,825,1485,1511]" name="Portugal" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Portugal</collectingCountry>
is best referred to as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Morawitz" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1059,1230,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibulare">
<emphasis box="[1059,1230,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">L. mandibulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until this situation has been clarified.
</paragraph>
